## ⚠️ PRODUCTION ENVIRONMENT WARNINGS

**THIS IS THE PRODUCTION ENVIRONMENT.**

### Repository Paths

- **Service Host**: Runs docker-compose-prod.yml (UI, API, postgres, monitoring)
- **Worker Hosts**: Runs workers via PM2 (celery, conversions, watch, metrics)
- **Secure Download Host**: Runs the secure download service

### Access Restrictions

You only have access to:
- The service host repo directory (code changes only)
- Worker host repo directories (code changes only)
- `/tmp` for temporary read/write/delete operations

**Note:** Paths beginning with data directories referenced in codebase/env vars only apply when `NODE_ENV='docker'` or `APP_ENV='docker'`. In proion, these paths do not exist. See `.ai/PRODUCTION_ENVIRONMENT.md` for details.

### Critical Restrictions

#### ❌ NEVER Allowed (Unless User Explicitly Permits):

**File System:**
- **ALWAYS** delete anything written to `/tmp` after work is done

**Database:**
- **NEVER** reset the database on service host

**Docker:**
- **NEVER** run ANY docker commands (not even read-only: `docker ps`, `docker logs`, etc.)
- **NEVER** exec into docker containers or restart them

**Workers:**
- **NEVER** restart/kill/stop workers (PM2 commands: `pm2 restart`, `pm2 stop`, `pm2 delete`)
- Can view logs: `pm2 logs`, `pm2 monit`
- Can enter poetry shell: `poetry shell`

**System Services:**
- **NEVER** restart system services (docker, nginx, apache, etc.)
- **NEVER** use sudo (you do NOT have sudo access)

**Git:**
- **NEVER** do git write operations (`git pull`, `git push`, `git rebase`, `git merge`, `git commit`)
- Can do read-only operations (`git status`, `git diff`, `git log`, `git reflog`, etc.)

**nodemon:**
- **NEVE* use nodemon in production (except UI service)
- Not allowed in Dockerfiles, package.json scripts, or any config files

#### ✅ Always Allowed:

- Safe read-only operations for debugging on any host
- Reading logs, viewing process status
- File inspection with `cat`, `grep`, `ls`, etc. (except `.env` files)
- Git read-only operations
- `poetry shell` in workers directory

### Host Restrictions

- You can only make **code changes** on appropriate hosts
- **Exception:** All restrictions can be overridden if user explicitly permits in chat

